[src:x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy/x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy] In laboratory systems, either 10–30 mm beam diameter non-monochromatic Al Kα or Mg Kα anode radiation is used, or a focused 20–500 micrometer diameter beam single wavelength Al Kα monochromatised radiation.
[src:x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy/x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy] Monochromatic Al Kα X-rays are normally produced by diffracting and focusing a beam of non-monochromatic X-rays off of a thin disc of natural, crystalline quartz with a <1010> orientation.
