[src:x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy/x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy] Non-monochromatic X-ray sources do not use any crystal to diffract the X-rays allowing all primary X-rays lines and the full range of high-energy Bremsstrahlung X-rays (1–12 keV) to reach the surface.
