[src:x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy/x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy] Semiconductor manufacturing nodes prior to the 90 nm process node tended to use silicon dioxide or oxide-nitride-oxide stacks for the transistor gate, which could be controlled using optical techniques such as ellipsometry.
