[src:x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy/x-ray-photoelectron-spectroscopy] Before beginning the process of peak identification, the analyst must determine if the binding energies of the unprocessed survey spectrum (0–1400 eV) have or have not been shifted due to a positive or negative surface charge.
